A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 University of Maryland Eastern Shore – Land–Grant Institution – Funding
3 (Land–Grant Equity and Accountability Act)
4 FOR the purpose of requiring, to address a certain funding disparity, that the Governor
5 include a certain appropriation to the University of Maryland Eastern Shore in the
6 annual budget bill each fiscal year until a certain total amount is appropriated; and
7 generally relating to funding for the University of Maryland Eastern Shore.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Education
10 Section 15–140
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Education
16 15–140.
17 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “UMES” MEANS THE UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND
18 EASTERN SHORE.
19 (B) (1) THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY FINDS THAT IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE
20 LETTER ISSUED TO THE GOVERNOR JOINTLY FROM THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF
