2 HOUSE BILL 941
1 EDUCATION AND THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE, DATED SEPTEMBER 18,
2 2023:
3 (I) THE SECOND MORRILL ACT OF 1890 REQUIRED STATES
4 CHOOSING TO OPEN A SECOND LAND–GRANT INSTITUTION FOR BLACK STUDENTS
5 TO PROVIDE AN EQUITABLE DISTRIBUTION OF FUNDS BETWEEN 1862 AND 1890
6 LAND–GRANT INSTITUTIONS;
7 (II) A FUNDING DISPARITY EXISTED FROM 1987 THROUGH 2020
8 BETWEEN UMES, THE STATE’S 1890 LAND–GRANT INSTITUTION, AND THE
9 UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND, COLLEGE PARK CAMPUS, THE STATE’S 1862
10 LAND–GRANT INSTITUTION;
11 (III) IF UMES RECEIVED THE SAME LEVEL OF STATE FUNDING
12 PER STUDENT AS THE UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND, COLLEGE PARK CAMPUS FROM
13 1987 THROUGH 2020, AN ADDITIONAL $321,181,312 WOULD HAVE BEEN AVAILABLE
14 FOR UMES; AND
15 (IV) THE FUNDING PROVIDED UNDER THIS SECTION SHALL
16 REMEDY THE FUNDING DISPARITY DESCRIBED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION.
17 (2) IT IS THE INTENT OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY THAT THE
18 FUNDING PROVIDED UNDER THIS SECTION BE APPROPRIATED EACH FISCAL YEAR IN
19 A MANNER THAT REMEDIES THE FUNDING DISPARITY AS SOON AS PRACTICABLE.
20 (C) (1) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2027 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER,
21 THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION
22 OF AT LEAST $5,000,000 TO UMES.
23 (2) FOR ANY FISCAL YEAR, THE AMOUNT APPROPRIATED TO UMES
24 UNDER THIS SUBSECTION MAY NOT BE LESS THAN THE AMOUNT APPROPRIATED IN
25 THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING FISCAL YEAR.
26 (3) FUNDS PROVIDED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE:
27 (I) APPROPRIATED EACH FISCAL YEAR UNTIL A TOTAL
28 AMOUNT OF $321,181,312 IS APPROPRIATED TO UMES; AND
29 (II) SUPPLEMENTAL TO, AND MAY NOT SUPPLANT, FUNDS
30 APPROPRIATED TO UMES IN THE STATE BUDGET.
31 (D) FUNDS PROVIDED UNDER THIS SECTION MAY BE USED FOR:

HOUSE BILL 941 3
1 (1) DEVELOPMENT OF INFRASTRUCTURE AND ACADEMIC
2 PROGRAMS;
3 (2) INVESTMENT IN FACULTY;
4 (3) SCHOLARSHIPS; AND
5 (4) ANY OTHER INSTITUTIONAL NEED IDENTIFIED BY UMES.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
7 1, 2025.

